<div class="container">

    <div class="card">
        <h2>What is Location?</h2>
        <p>
            Location explains where a place is found on Earth. It helps us identify
            the exact position of a place using geographic tools.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
        <h2>Types of Location</h2>
        <p>
            There are two main types of location:
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Absolute Location:</strong> Uses latitude and longitude to pinpoint a place.</li>
                <li><strong>Relative Location:</strong> Describes a place based on its surroundings or nearby landmarks.</li>
            </ul>
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
        <h2>Example</h2>
        <p>
            For example, Accra’s absolute location is approximately 5.6037° N, 0.1870° W, 
            while its relative location is along the Gulf of Guinea, east of Tema.
        </p>
    </div>

</div>

